The course gives an overview of different texts (e.g. description, short story, letters, essay etc.), their vocabulary, structure and style. Attention is paid to text organisation, commonly misspelt words and punctuation. Students practise writing and analyse tasks which are suitable for basic school students.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to teach students to write and analyse different texts as well as enlarge their vocabulary and develop stylistic skills. To give students ideas how to use different writing activities in English lessons at basic school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course a student  * will know the main features of different texts (description, a short story, essay, report, poem etc.) and pay attention to their specific features; *will compose different texts, using appropriate vocabulary and style; *will know the main rules of punctuation and use punctuation marks correctly; *will know the spelling of difficult words and can correct them; *will analyse and evaluate their peers' work; *will know the types of different writing tasks and can analyse them;  *can choose suitable writing tasks to develop students' writing skills in a basic school English class.
